{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/manifests/colette-tougas-at-ultimatum-festival-1985-05-01.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"en":["Colette Tougas at Ultimatum Festival 1985-05-01"]},"homepage":[{"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985","type":"Text","label":{"en":["Colette Tougas at Ultimatum Festival 1985-05-01"]},"format":"text/html"}],"metadata":[{"label":{"en":["Description"]},"value":{"en":["The following is a transcription of the Colette Tougas set at Ultimatum, Wednesday, May 1st, 1985 at the Foufounes Electriques. Tougas performs \"Clara La Brune\", an alluring, dramatic monologue with a refrain sung throughout. In his memoirs, Alan Lord counts the performance as one of the festival highlights, recalling \"Writer Colette Tougas singing a capella the sultry Modesty in her smoldering breathy voice, which I just had to put on the festival's documentary LP...\" Colette Tougas is a translator, writer of fiction and of essays, recently contributing art criticism to the online magazine, Ciel Variable. She is the author of Le Porphyre de la Rue Dezery (1985)."]}},{"label":{"en":["Language"]},"value":{"en":["English"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/colette_tougas_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/18","type":"Canvas","duration":1139,"annotations":[{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/manifests/colette_tougas_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01-canvas18-1","type":"AnnotationPage","label":{"en":["Default"]},"items":[{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://spokenweb.github.io/Ultimatumi1985/colette_tougas_at_ultimatum_festival_1985_05_01/canvas/18/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Silence.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Recording","format":"te